P(x,N)=\sum_{k=1}^N x^k\frac{d^k}{dx^k}
x\in\left[-1,+1\right]
N
-1\le x\le1
N=2
x^2\frac{d^2y}{dx^2} + x\frac{dy}{dx} + y = 0
y_0 = y
y_1 = y_0'
= x \frac{dy_0}{dx}
y_1' = x\frac{dy_1}{dx} = x\frac{d}{dx}(x\frac{dy_0}{dx}) = x\frac{dy_0}{dx} + x^2\frac{d^2 y_0}{dx^2} = y_1 + x^2\frac{d^2y_0}{dx^2}
x^2\frac{d^2y}{dx^2} = -y_0 - x\frac{dy_0}{dx} = -y_0 - y_1
y_1' = y_1 - y_0 -y_1 = -y_0 
